Date: Thu, 25 Oct 2007 17:35:35 +0100
From: David Howells <>
Subject: [PATCH 19/31] IGET: Stop ISOFS from using read_inode() [try #5]
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2007/10/25/247

Stop the ISOFS filesystem from using read_inode().  Make isofs_read_inode()
return an error code, and make isofs_iget() pass it on.
Signed-off-by: David Howells <dhowells@redhat.com>
---
 fs/isofs/inode.c |   25 +++++++++++++++++--------
